From 45d7d675d799593fcfab5eb9fcca653345e15678 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Sep 2025 00:35:24 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Suppress error log for zero RX
 header length in monitor mode

Currently, driver parses RX header TLVs from the monitor destination
ring and returns -EINVAL when the RX header length is zero or invalid. This
results in frequent error messages such as -EINVAL flooding the console,
especially in multi-client scenarios.

In these cases, the hardware does not provides a buffer address TLV for the
MSDU when the RX header length is zero, which is a valid scenario and does
not indicate a fatal error. The excessive error logging is unnecessary and
can obscure other important messages.

Fix this by returning 0 (success) instead of -EINVAL when the RX header
length is zero, thereby suppressing the error log and allowing normal PPDU
processing to continue.

Error Print:
ath12k_wifi7_pci 0002:01:00.0: mon_rx_parse_dest failed with ret -22

TLV sequence:

HAL_RX_PPDU_START
tlv_tag : 0x000000C0
tlv_len : 0x00000018

HAL_RX_PPDU_START_USER_INFO
tlv_tag : 0x00000136
tlv_len : 0x00000020

HAL_RX_HEADER
tlv_tag : 0x000000C9
tlv_len : 0x00000008

HAL_RX_MPDU_START
tlv_tag : 0x000000C2
tlv_len : 0x00000040

HAL_RX_MSDU_END
tlv_tag : 0x000000C5
tlv_len : 0x00000018

HAL_RX_MPDU_END
tlv_tag : 0x000000C3
tlv_len : 0x00000010

HAL_RX_USER_PPDU_END
tlv_tag : 0x000000D4
tlv_len : 0x00000000

HAL_RX_PPDU_END
tlv_tag : 0x000000C1
tlv_len : 0x00000280

HAL_RX_PPDU_END_USER_STATS
tlv_tag : 0x00000117
tlv_len : 0x00000058

HAL_RX_PPDU_END_STATUS_DONE
tlv_tag : 0x00000125
tlv_len : 0x00000008

Patch-Dependency:
0511-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-validate-RX-status-header-le.patch

Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
index f9941f7..1b81f8e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
@@ -249,7 +249,7 @@ ath12k_wifi7_dp_mon_parse_status_rx_hdr(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev,
 	if (unlikely(frag_len <= 0) || frag_len > DP_MON_RX_HDR_LEN) {
 		ath12k_dbg(dp_pdev->dp->ab, ATH12K_DBG_DP_MON_RX,
 			   "invalid rx header length: %d", frag_len);
-		return -EINVAL;
+		return 0;
 	}
 
 	if (!ppdu_info->mpdu_info.mpdu_start_received) {
-- 
